import fcsparser
import sklearn.cluster
from joblib import load
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
meta, df = fcsparser.parse("D:/Experiment_data/weizmann/EhV/201/aggregates/non_intensity_T0234567_R123.fcs")
df_meta = df[["label", "replicate", "timepoint"]].astype(int)
df_meta["timepoint"] = df_meta["timepoint"].map(lambda a: meta["timepoint"].split(",")[a])
df_meta["replicate"] = df_meta["replicate"].map(lambda a: meta["replicate"].split(",")[a])
df = df.drop(columns=["label", "replicate", "timepoint"])
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
kmeans = sklearn.cluster.MiniBatchKMeans()
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
batch_size = 5000
n_batches = int(numpy.ceil(df.shape[0]/batch_size))

print(f"Fitting K-means on {n_batches}")
for i in range(n_batches):
    if i % 10 == 0:
        print(f"Batch {i}")
    if i-1 == n_batches:
        end = df.shape[0]
    else:
        end = (i+1)*batch_size
    
    kmeans.partial_fit(df.iloc[i*batch_size:end])

    choices = numpy.nonzero(output == cluster)[0]
    indices.extend(list(numpy.random.choice(choices, replace=False, size=count)))
